    <div id="entry-423">
	<div class="entry-header">
		<h2 class="asset-name entry-title"><a href="http://www.encs.concordia.ca/news-and-events/entry.php?a=2011/11/fluid-dynamics-image-helps-honour-remembrance-day.php">Fluid dynamics image helps honour Remembrance Day</a></h2>
		<div class="entry-meta" title="2011-11-09T16:46:06-05:00">Wednesday Nov  9, 2011
                </div>
	</div>

	<div class="entry-content">
	
		<div class="entry-body">
			<a href="http://www.me.concordia.ca/facultyandstaff/full-timefaculty/hoi-dick-ng.php">Hoi Dick "Eddie" Ng</a>, associate professor from the <a href="http://www.me.concordia.ca/index.php">Department of Mechanical and Industrial Engineering</a>, and undergraduate student, Anna Shchetinina, have submitted a visually stunning and technically amazing artistic image for the Gallery of Fluid Motion competition. <i><br /><br /></i><div align="center"><img alt="HDNg-2.jpg" src="http://newsfeed.encs.concordia.ca/encs_test/HDNg-2.jpg" class="mt-image-center" style="text-align: center; display: block; margin: 0 auto 20px;" height="428" width="440" /><font style="font-size: 0.8em;"><i>image by A. Shchetinina &amp; H.D. Ng (Concordia University, Montr√©al, Canada)</i></font><br /></div><br />Given the timing of this year's competition, the image they chose is especially apropos: although the image actually shows the dynamics of an imploding circular water wave, it looks surprisingly like a Remembrance Day poppy. <br /><br />The annual competition is hosted by the Fluid Dynamics division of the American Physical Society and will be held this year at Baltimore in Nov. 20-22, 2011. Dr. Ng his students have entered the competition for several years running now and often perform well against the 50 or so entries that are submitted from around the globe. <br /><br />You can learn more about how this amazing image was created by visiting the <a href="http://www.aps.org/units/dfd/pressroom/gallery/ng11.cfm">APS website.</a><br /> <div><br /></div>
		</div>
	
	</div>
